com.vmware.vapi.metadata.metamodel.resource

Interface Model

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, ModelTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ModelStub

    public interface Model
extends Service, ModelTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Model interface provides methods to retrieve information about models.

    A structure is used as a model if it is used for persisting data about an entity. Some of the fields in the model structure are also used for creating indexes for querying.

    One or more services can operate on the same resource type. One or more services can provide the model structure for an entity of this resource type. Using Model interface you can retrieve the list of all the structure elements that are model structures for a given resource type.

    • Method Detail

      • list

        Model.ListInvocation list(java.lang.String resourceId)
        Returns the set of identifiers for the structure elements that are models for the resource type corresponding to resourceId.

        The Structure interface provides methods to retrieve more details about the structure elements corresponding to the identifiers returned by this method.

        Invocation Result:
        The set of identifiers for the models that are associated with the resource type in resourceId. The return value will contain identifiers for the resource type: com.vmware.vapi.structure.

        Operation Errors:
        NotFound - if the resource type associated with resourceId does not exist.

        Parameters:
        resourceId - Identifier of the resource type. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vapi.resource.
        Returns:
        instance of Model.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
